default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe impact of the scope changes to legal aid for prison law are devastating when placed in the wider
default context of the issues faced by those in justice system.  The prison population remains too high, with a large proportion of people with high needs and/or serving
default indeterminate sentences trapped
default in the system.  The population is set to rise as professional
defaults with the experience to managing prisoners are squeezed out of the system
default.
default&#xa0;
default1.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe complaints system is inadequate as a substitution for legal representation.
default It is lengthy, under-resourced, bureaucratic and only used by adult male prisoners who have years of experience. The Prisons and Probation Ombudsman is not a statutory post and lacks the powers to enforce his decisions.
default&#xa0;
default1.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIt is neither desirab
defaultle nor realis
defaulttic for prisoners 
defaultto be told to rely on Judicial Review as a safety net in the absence of criminal legal aid for prison law.
default 
