default2.1
default              
defaultFounded in 1866, the Howard League
default for Penal Reform
default is the oldest penal reform
default charity in the 
defaultworld
default. The Howard L
defaulteague has 7,000 members, including prisoners and their families, lawyers, 
defaultcriminal justice professionals and academics. The Howard League has consultative status with both the United Nations and the Council of Europe. It is an independent charity and accepts no grant funding from the UK government.
default&#xa0;
default2.2 
default              
defaultThe Howard League campaigns for less crime, safer communities and fewer people in prison. We achieve these objectives through conducting and commissioning research and investigations aimed at revealing underlying problems and discovering new solutions
default to issues of public concern. The Howard League’s objectives and principles underlie and inform the charity’s parliamentary work, research, legal and participation work as well as its projects.
default 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default2.3 
default              
defaultSince 2002 the Howard League has provided the only leg
defaultal service dedicated to representing children in custody. We also provide a dedicated legal service for young adults in prison (under 21) and, where appropriate, comment on the particular considerations that are required to ensure that this age group is de
defaultalt with fairly and appropriately.
default  
default&#xa0;
default2.4
default              
defaultWe have therefore drawn upon our lawyers’ experience in practice as well as our expertise in this policy area when submitting this written evidence
default.
default 
default&#xa0;
default2.5
default              
defaultThe Howard League is a member of the Association of Prison 
defaultLawyers and 
defaultJustRights
default. We
default endorse their evidence. Consequently, this submission deals with issues within our particular field of expertise and experience.
